This dish turned out very well. I might switch the white onion for a red onion for color and to round out the flavor since the zucchini is so mild, otherwise, the flavors were nice and bright on a cold winter's night. Served this with green beans boiled, then added good olive oil and salt. This one I'll add to my recipe box.

Rating: 3
The only change I made to this recipe was to cut down the salt by 1/2. Both my husband and I agreed that this one is a keeper. I'll be making it again --- when I find halibut on sale.

Rating: 1
This was delicious, however... if you have a sensitive stomach, don't go near it! I get really bad stomach aches from broccoli and cucumber, among other things. Apparently raw zucchini has a similar effect. I was curled up in a ball within an hour of eating this.

